  "articleSummary": "This tutorial introduces JavaScript Promises as a standardized mechanism for reliably managing the success or failure outcomes of asynchronous operations. Targeted at beginner to intermediate JavaScript developers, the article covers native promise-returning APIs like `fetch` and `axios`, alongside core creation methods (`Promise.resolve()` and the `new Promise()` constructor) and essential instance/utility methods (`.then()`, `.catch()`, `Promise.all()`, and `Promise.race()`). Framed around a binary success/failure execution diagram, the piece maintains a straightforward, instructional tone while emphasizing practical patterns for wrapping values and chaining async results.",
